  					<td align=center valign="top" width=100%><br>
  						<!--#beginContent#-->
  						<table align='center' cellpadding=5 width='85%'>  <tr><td class='spti2' width='100%'>PLAYER STRATEGY - SHAMAN</td></tr>  <tr><td width='100%' class='db'><font class='dbti'>SHAMAN LEVELLING</font> - <small>Kodzakis, Torvonnilous</td></tr>
  <tr><td width='100%' class='db'><p><b>Two Ways of Levelling that Shaman</b><br><br>

<em>The Good Way.</em><br>
  Get yourself to Warsliks Woods. Go right out the door and turn left. There is a trooper at the edge of the forest line. I can't remember his name, but he has now become your best friend (some friend I was, I can't remember his name). Use burst of flame, (or anything to pull with) and pull goblin whelps to you while you are standing about 10 feet from the trooper. If the goblin whelp comes with some extra friends just try to smack at least one of them before you think you need to run. If you need to, just take a few steps towards the trooper and he lays the smack down on them and you rest, cast inner fire and healing while you are resting. Keep on doing this until you can take the goblin watchers and scouts. <br>
<br>
Here's where the experience is doubled: Take down the watchers with signal torches. Get three of them and take them to this Iksar Captain Gideen on the second floor balcony of a small building located real close to your location there. He will give you exp, coin, and a bandage that you can sell or use. This works up till level 7. What I did was to kill until I had no more slots for inventory, then I dropped all of them on the good captain, 3 AT A TIME, of course.<br><br>

The Kicker: You get Positive faction with both Cabilis AND Firiona Vie for killing any Goblins. So in the EQ world, if you kill enough of the little pointy eared devils, you can walk proud in the land of the pasty pallys of Firiona Vie. I know it can be done 'cause I saw an Iksar warrior walking amongst them somewhere above lvl 20 with my Ranger. Im not sure when it happens but I couldn't at lvl 9 so I'm gonna keep on playing soccer with goblin hedz until I do.<br><br>

The way I did it to boost the levels faster.
  At lvl 1 I headed out the door, with much care, popped in at the Forest Giant Fort in Warsliks Woods and asked to loot a Forest Giant Hammer (no drop, 10dmg, 35dly) from one of the camp groups there. I eventually came across a druid that let me loot one while he was looking for items for his quest, I think. It can't be sold or traded due to being a no drop, so people are generally willing to let you loot one. As a Shammy with 90 strength buffed I was hitting for 12-17 sometimes 20 damage with it.
<br><br>
The real trick to this way is to find the best weapon to do the most damage whether it's 1 or 2hb or piercing, or whatever your 'bag' is for your class. You might be able to find, when you get enough, a bronze mace for 6 plat from one of the vendors in Cabilis.<br><br>

<b>Some things to consider.</b><br>
- Skeletons will agro to you no matter what lvl you are.<br>
- Goblins will run when they get beat on pretty bad so watch out. If they can, they will bring back their big brothers to settle the score.<br>
- If you want to, get someone to bind you right inside the door to Warsliks Woods, it will save you time on traveling back for corpse recovery and when you get higher you can go to the Lake of Ill Omen with a shorter travel.<br>
- The watchers sometimes drop a red headband with negative charisma and +dex 3AC, this can be saved for a later use - this is a long way off but the Ranger Guild Captain in Firiona Vie takes 4 for exp quest. At lvl 9 I had 6 boxes full of them so I stopped there waiting to be able to get high enough to turn them in. I may end up destroying them 'cause they are no drop and are taking space in the bank.<br>
- The torch quest is good exp up until lvl 7 then its minimal, but still do-able.<br>
- You can also buy signal watcher torches from the vendors everywhere. They are cheap, a few silver so, if you got a few bits that you want to spend, it may be worth it.<br>
- The Goblin Thief drops a part of a poem that is worthless to anyone other than warrior, it's for a warrior quest, same as the Goblin Hunter Javelin off the Goblin Hunters.<br>
<br>
I can't think of anything else other than buy some armor when you get a chance, I saved what I could and went straight to leather. You can got the cloth route then go to leather and on up. And buy your spells if they apply to you as you progress.<br>
<br>
Good Journey and Safe Travels<br></p>
		</td></tr>
